;
;---------------------------------------------------
;
; coding
;
;---------------------------------------------------
;
;
C00,Instrument Cluster (J285) Coding
C01,??xxx: Equipment
C02,+01 = Brake Pad Warning installed
C03,+02 = Seatbelt Warning installed
C04,+04 = Washer Fluid Warning installed
C05,+08 = Check Lamp for "Lamp/Bulp Diagnostic" installed
C06,+16 = Check Lamp for "Open Door(s)" installed
C07,xx?xx: Country
C08,0 = Germany (DE) / 1 = Europe (EU) / 2 = USA (US) / 3 = Canada (CDN)
C09,4 = Great Britain (GB) / 5 = Japan (JP) /6 = Saudi Arabia (SA) / 7 = Australia (AUS)
C10,xxx?x: Service Intervals
C11,0 = fixed Service Intervals without Oil Level/Temperature Sensor (PR-QG0)
C12,1 = flexible Service Intervals with Oil Level/Temperature Sensor (PR-QG1)
C13,2 = fixed Service Intervals with Oil Level/Temperature Sensor (PR-QG2)
C14,3 = without Service Intervals (USA/Canada)
C15,xxxx?: Engine Type (Distance Impulse Number)
C16,1 = All Engine/Transmission Combinations (Signal Source CAN: 23984)
C17,1 = 1.4l@55kW Autom./1.4l@55kW TDI-PD/1.9l@74kW TDI-PD (Signal Source Speed Sensor: 3775)
C18,2 = 1.2l@40-47kW/1.4l@55kW Manual/1.4l@74kW (Signal Source Speed Sensor: 3904)
C19,2 = 2.0l@85kW/1.9l@47 SDI/1.9l@96kW TDI-PD (Signal Source Speed Sensor: 3904)
;
;
;---------------------------------------------------
;
; login
;
;---------------------------------------------------
;
;
L00,Instrument Cluster (J285) Login
L01,13861 = Adaptation Enabling
L02, 
L03,Prior to Key Learning or adapting a used replacement
L04,Instrument Cluster the Vehicle specific PIN/SKC (Login)
L05,of the replacement Instrument Cluster has to be used
L06,to enable the adaptation.
L07,You'll find the PIN/SKC on the Key Tag of the additional
L08,Key (of the Donor Car) or you can acquire it through your
L09,responsible Distribution Center or Importer.
;
;
